Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel).

Pop the chunks onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, season with
@salt{} and @ground black pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single
layer. TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, in a large #bowl{}, combine the @mayonnaise{64%grams},
@wholegrain mustard{17%grams} (use less if you'd prefer things milder),
@cider vinegar{15%milliliters}, @hard Italian style cheese{20%grams}(grated)
and half the @honey{30%grams}. TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop it in a
#bowl{} of hot water for ~{1%minute}.

Cut the @medium tomatoes{2} into 2cm chunks and toss through the dressing.
Set aside.

Trim the @baby gem lettuce{1}, separate the leaves, then tear into bite-sized
pieces - you'll add it to the dressing later.

Tear the @ciabatta{1} into roughly 2cm chunks. Pop the ciabatta onto another
baking tray in a single layer.

Drizzle with oil, season with salt and ground black pepper and toss to coat.
Bake the croutons on the middle shelf until golden, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @British smoked bacon lardons{90%grams}. Stir-fry until
golden, ~{4-5%minutes}, then remove from the heat.

Stir the remaining honey through the cooked bacon.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook bacon thoroughly.

When everything's ready, add the baby gem, roasted potatoes and croutons to the
large bowl with your dressing and tomatoes. Toss to coat.

Taste and season with salt and ground black pepper if needed.

Share the creamy potato salad between your serving bowls.

Scatter over the honeyed bacon to finish.

Enjoy!